okie cutter (10 cm), cut out 12 pastry rounds and press into mini tartlet tins. Dock each pastry case with a fork, line with baking paper and fill with pie weights, rice or dried beans.  Bake for 12 minutes (180°C) or until dry to the touch. Set aside to cool completely, then remove from tins. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Lime curd"},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place all Lime curd ingredients into mixing bowl and cook <b>20 min\/80°C\/speed 3<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Spoon 2 teaspoons of curd into base of each pastry case, then place onto a baking tray (30 x 40 cm). Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Meringue"},{"content":"Increase oven to 200°C. <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <b>2 min\/70°C\/speed 3<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, until stiff peaks form."},{"content":"Add vanilla paste and cook <b>2 min\/60°C\/speed 3<b>, adding icing sugar 1 tablespoon at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Cook for a further <b>5 min\/60°C\/speed 3<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"Transfer meringue into a piping bag fitted with a plain nozzle (1 cm) and decorate the top of each tart as desired. Bake for 10 minutes (200°C) or until meringue is lightly browned. Remove from oven and transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 1 hour) before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own icing sugar, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>.","To save time, make the lime curd while pastry cases are baking and cooling."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","2h 40m","12 portions"]}